data_list.name: Uzbekistan
data_list.description: The first record of the building which now the restaurant occupies dates back to the end of the 19th century, according to the Moscow historical archives. Initially there was a tavern which was very famous in the city. Then the building was sold and a French café was opened instead of the tavern. During the stern post-revolutionary years there was an officer cafeteria and in 1951 the ministry of trade of the Uzbek SSR decided to open there Uzbekistan restaurant. This date marked the beginning of the restaurant’s history In 1997 new proprietors of the restaurant – Arkady Novikov, Igor Kofman and Vladimir Lisavetsky – decided to breathe new life in this place and began the complete restoration of this unique building. The interior of Uzbekistan restaurant was redesigned by palace restorers specially invited from Tashkent.

data_list.name: La Bottega Siciliana
data_list.description:
Nino Graziano and Igor Vitoshinsky present the cuisine of Sicily in the very center of Moscow.
Sicily is the brightest and hottest region in all of Italy, and its gastronomy clearly feels oriental juiciness and spice.

Chef Claudio Pirovano, a student of Nino, cooks fresh pasta, vegetables and selected seafood, Stefano Prosperini bakes real Italian pizza in a wood-burning oven. And, of course, no Sicilian dinner will be complete without incomparable desserts and real gelato – our ice cream, rightfully considered the best in Moscow.

The restaurant is divided into 3 parts: a pastry shop at the entrance with high chairs where you can drink coffee, take desserts to take away; the main hall with a view of the open kitchen; a more private hall with a fireplace.

data_list.name: Korchma Taras Bulba
data_list.description: Korchma "Taras Bulba" - is an atmospheric interior and delicious national cuisine. The interior of the tavern is the atmosphere of a Ukrainian house with a huge oven, they laid brick and carefully whitewashed, homespun doormat, embroidered tablecloths, utensils and old photographs. Add a vibrance national costumes worn by the waiters. If you read once books N. In. Gogol, when he came to the tavern, fully feel like visiting your favorite character. From the variety of the menu dazzled. If you can't eat, but the desire to try all the dishes you have not left, order a takeaway. The first is to try the dumplings, eat them, dipped in sour cream, as did the famous character from the book Gogol. Sweet berries, poppy seeds, cabbage, potatoes with mushrooms, cottage cheese, salmon with dill, meat is all the toppings. If you can not decide, then order cannon sweet dumplings, a great opportunity to try almost everything at once. The bread here is baked themselves, moreover, even the flour of its own production, making cakes tavern like this fragrant and beautiful. From our own farm economy "the Cossack" bring to the tavern fresh butter, thick cream, cottage cheese, honey. Only these natural products are used in the dishes, they can also be ordered to your table. In the tavern well come to fine dining, impress guests while walking, are comfortable to spend time as a family, with friends. If you want to organize an unusual, themed party, even a wedding, even a kid's birthday party, you'll be very happy.

data_list.name: Ugolek
data_list.description: Ugolеk is the restaurant of Uilliam Lamberti and Ilya Tyutenkov. We would like to tell you about ovens we use to prepare food at our restaurant. These are antiquarian restored cast-irone ovens that were made in the USA in the XIX-the beginning of the XX centuries. These ovens were the heart of every house, hotel or even saloon. They were used for cooking, heating, people gave them names and for every oven a special design was created. All the dishes at the restaurant are made only in ovens or grilled, except some cold collations of course. Everything is cooked on firewood, that's why food has its particular flavor. Style of food is brutal and a bit retro, and also modern knowledge of product's qualities are used. The kitchen is headed by well-known already in Moscow and well proved Italian Dgiacomo Lombardi.

Awarded as well as by the world rating of The World's 50 Best Restaurants, as well as by the guides Gault & Millau and Conde Nast Traveler.​ Chef Dimitry Eremeev has been in charge of the TURANDOT’s kitchen since 2008. Previously, he worked for the Presidential Office of the Russian Federation and in "Cafe Pushkin”.
